{
  "name": "The Panic Table - Panic Effect",
  "formula": "1d1",
  "description": "<p>The horrific nature of the Forge takes a toll on any spacer’s mind. Sometimes, keeping your cool under extreme pressure is not possible. A Panic check determines if you’re able to keep control of the situation without losing it.</p><p>A miss with a match triggers a Panic Check. To make a Panic Check, roll a d6 and attempt to roll under your current Spirit. If you roll more than your current Spirit you fail, and you look up your result on the Panic Table.</p><p>Some results prompt you to gain a condition. Record that condition on your character sheet. To clear it, you must Hearten. On a hit, instead of gaining Spirit, you may decide to clear a condition.</p>",
